def: Having similar proportions, similar relations, or similardifferences of composition; -- said specifically of groups or serieswhich differ by a constant difference; as, ethane, ethylene, anacetylene, or their analogous compounds, form an isologous series.
The dissection of an animal while alive, for the purpose ofmaking physiological investigations.
A prayer; an invocation; a religious formula; a charm. [India]
One who accepts or maintains the dogma of papal infallibility.
A nitrogenous hydrocarbon base, C13H9N, analogous tophenanthrene and quinoline.
An interior corner; a nook; hence, an angular recess or hollowbend in a mountain, river, cliff, or the like. [Western & Southern U.S.] D. S. Jordan.
A sort of pear, called also the red butter pear, from itssmooth, delicious, soft pulp.
